pTitle: 18 cu. ft. Top Freezer Refrigerator in White
rText: I bought this as a brand-new unit and had it delivered but not installed. When I went to roll it into place a screw on the underside that was installed at the wrong angle and not completely tightened down scratched up my floors. Upon further inspection my "brand new" unit had dents on the top, the top two fridge door bracket screw holes were stripped and had helicoils installed(badly) to try and fix them, then the new screw was cross-threaded into the helicoil. So either Frigidaire or Home Depot sold me a damaged, badly-repaired fridge as new. I've now lost a half-day of work getting their tech to come out and confirm the defects. I'll lose another half-day getting this thing picked up. And I'm having to go through Frigidaire's claim department to get my damaged floor fixed.
rTitle: Multiple defects, clearly a repaired fridge sold as new, it caused damage to my house

pTitle: 25.54 cu. ft. Side by Side Refrigerator in Stainless Steel
rText: Love the look, size and interior space. Wish the ice/H20 dispenser box was a little bigger vertically, and the external tray was removable for ease of cleaning, but not enough to fuss about, it does give more room inside for actual freezer space. The ice maker is amazing, but it tends to toss out cubes from the right side of the bin, I can live with that. It does make some groaning sounds at times, as some of the reviews said. Not a problem, at least I know it's my new fridge, not my old, dead relatives giving me lip because I got rid of a "perfectly good old fridge." I'm happy, and when I need other new appliances, I will go Frigidaire all the way.
